<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06243055 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06243055 </ACCESS><CAPTION>  Map, Photo; PHOTO: Paul Kitagaki Jr. -- Mercury News; WITNESS QUESTIONED --Police officer Donna Arndt, right, interviews Monique Boyd, 11, who had beenvisiting a neighbor of Lisa Marie Weidenhofer, whose child was taken Thursdayevening from her South San Jose apartment.; MAP: Mercury News; Baby kidnappedin San Jose  </CAPTION><DESCRIPT>  INFANT; KIDNAPPING; VICTIM; SAN-JOSE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A 4-day-old girl was abducted from a South San Jose apartment Thursday eveningby a female intruder who apparently hid in a bedroom and beat the baby'smother on the head, police said.;   The mother, Lisa Marie Weidenhofer, 24,was tending her two small children in the living room of her apartment onSeven Trees Boulevard, when she heard a noise in the bedroom and went in toinvestigate.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  4-DAY-OLD INFANT KIDNAPPED IN S.J.FEMALE INTRUDER ATTACKS MOTHER, THEN TAKES NEWBORN  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     The woman hit Weidenhofer several times on the head with a blunt object,threatened her, closed the bedroom door and fled.;   When Weidenhofer emerged,she found that her newborn daughter, Brynn, who had been lying in a sleeper onthe living room couch, was gone. Her other child, 19-month-old Kimber, was nottaken.;   &quot;Nothing as far as food or liquid was taken for the child, not evena blanket, so obviously we feel the child's life is in danger,&quot; said San Josepolice spokeswoman Veronica Damon. &quot;We don't think this woman can care for thechild.&quot;;   The baby has black hair, fair skin and blue eyes. She was wearing ablue dress and a disposable diaper and had bare feet. She weighs 8 pounds andis about 20 inches long.;   The mother described the kidnapper as either alight-skinned Hispanic or Anglo woman, 22 to 25 years old, about 5-feet-5 to5-feet-7, 150 to 170 pounds.;   The mother told police that the woman has alarge belly, large breasts and long, permed dark hair that flows past hershoulders. She has a deep voice and speaks English. She was last seen wearinga white T-shirt and blue jeans. Witnesses saw her running toward Seven TreesBoulevard about 5:50 p.m. from the Capitol Park Apartments.;   &quot;We're clearlyoperating on the assumption that it was a stranger abduction,&quot; Capt. ScottSeaman said.;   Police were still searching the area on foot and by helicopterlate Thursday, Damon said. They also issued bulletins describing thekidnapper.;   Weidenhofer was taken to Kaiser-Santa Teresa hospital, wherefriends said her daughter was born Sunday.;   A nursing supervisor said shewas in stable condition late Thursday. She was being treated for cuts on herhead and injuries to her forearm that she apparently got trying to shieldherself from the blows.;   The father of the abducted child, Tim Gaeta, 20,was at the apartment complex about an hour before the kidnapping, police said.But he left on personal business and did not come back until it was over, saidSeaman.;   Several witnesses reported seeing someone running from theapartment.;   One 11-year-old girl, who was visiting relatives said she lookedout of her second-story apartment after hearing a commotion next door and sawsomeone walking briskly away. But she said the person she saw was a man and hewas not carrying a baby.;   &quot;He looked like a girl. You had to look again tosee that he was a man,&quot; Monique Boyd said. &quot;All of a sudden, I heard somebodyscreaming, 'My baby! My baby!' &quot;  </TEXT><BYLINE>  LAURA KURTZMAN AND RODNEY FOO, Mercury News Staff Writers  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final Street  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910830  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Friday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  1A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><FEATURE>  PHOTO; MAP  </FEATURE><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  560  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Friday, August